>should I print out guidelines
Do it like this. The crop marks should be on the cut lines, but outside the printed area. The guillotine has its own straight edge, so there's no need for the line to go all the way, it's just there to align the straight edge.

You want one cut line for each border, don't share cut lines between the cards.

You need to add bleed: boring colour that goes over the cut line because printing is never accurate to the sub-millimetre.
